The paper discusses the approaches and preferences of scientists and engineers when searching for software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The survey was conducted across various scientific and engineering fields, including cybernetics (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and digital libraries (cs.DL). Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to the paper.
